"SECTION2_PARAGRAPH1" = "The first step is to check your hearing with a quick, painless test. This can be done by an audiologist in their office or on your own with certain AirPods Pro.";
"SECTION1_PARAGRAPH2" = "While exposure to loud sounds can accelerate hearing loss, it typically happens a little bit at a time. Many people don’t realize they’ve lost their hearing until there’s a significant difference. As a result, hearing loss often goes untreated.";
"SECTION3_PARAGRAPH4" = "In addition to hearing aids, there are also things you can do to support your ability to hear. Seating yourself in a corner can help isolate sounds to the ones you want to hear. If one of your ears has better hearing than the other, try turning that ear toward what you’d like to hear.";
"SECTION3_PARAGRAPH2" = "When you first start using a hearing aid, it takes some time to get used to. Your ears and brain need to adjust to the presence and sound levels of certain sounds you used to miss entirely. Using your hearing aids consistently can help you get more comfortable and make them part of your routine.";
